{
  "texts": [
    "While accuracy is not essential to some tasks, such as creative ideation and some writing or administrative tasks, accuracy is of utmost importance when using an LLM in factual question answering tasks such as question answering against databases or knowledge graphs (Zhang et al., 2023; Nooralahzadeh et al., 2024; Fürst et al., 2024).",
    "Assume that we have a knowledge graph (KG) about concerts and stadiums as shown in Figure 1.",
    "Further, assume that we want to answer the natural language question Show the stadium name and the number of concerts in each stadium.",
    "The major task of KGQA is to translate the natural language question into the formal query language that the KG supports, such as SPARQL.",
    "LLMs being used as KGQA systems tend to hallucinate incorrect class names, property names and literals in the generated SPARQL queries."
  ]
}